dialogue.speaker: Dogbert
dialogue.text: I've decided to dedicate my life to the less fortunate.

dialogue.speaker: Dilbert
dialogue.text: That's very noble of you, Dogbert. Will you be working with the homeless or perhaps the hungry?

dialogue.speaker: Dogbert
dialogue.text: I thought I'd start with people who didn't buy real estate in the 70s, maybe work my way up to that other stuff.
